definitions.definition: A set A such that every element of A is also an element of S .
examples: The set of integers is a subset of the set of real numbers .

The set { a , b } {\displaystyle \lbrace a,b\rbrace } is a both a subset and a proper subset of { a , b , c } {\displaystyle \lbrace a,b,c\rbrace } while the set { a , b , c } {\displaystyle \lbrace a,b,c\rbrace } is a subset of { a , b , c } {\displaystyle \lbrace a,b,c\rbrace } but not a proper subset of { a , b , c } {\displaystyle \lbrace a,b,c\rbrace } .
definitions.label_groups: set theory , of a set S

definitions.definition: A group of things or people, all of which are in a specified larger group.
examples: We asked a subset of the population of the town for their opinion.

main_definition: ( set theory , of a set S ) A set A such that every element of A is also an element of S .
